                    <msContents>
                        
                        <summary>The <title>Trailokyavijayakavaca</title> from the <title>Kubjikātantra</title>;
                        this is presumably identical with the <title>Trailokyamaṅgalavagalāmukhīkavaca</title> from the
                        <title>Kubjikātantra</title> (<abbr>NCC</abbr>, vol. 4, p. 199) and the <title>Trailokyavijayakavaca</title>
                        or <title>Bagalāmukhīkavaca</title> (<abbr>NCC</abbr>, vol. 8, p. 279). 
                            
                        In 21 verses, in the form of a dialogue between Bhairavī and Śiva.</summary>
                        
                        <textLang mainLang="sa">Sanskrit</textLang>
                        
                        <msItem xml:id="Alpha_2081">
                            <title>Trailokyavijayakavaca</title>
                            
                            <incipit> <locus>F. 1v</locus>
                                <!-- Transcript -->
                                śrīvagalāmukhīdevyai namaḥ ||
                                śrībhairavy uvāca ||
                                    sarvavidyāsvarūpā yā
                                    kathitā vagalāmukhī
                                    asyāś ca kavacaṃ nātha
                                    kṛpayā me prakāśaya ||1||
                            </incipit>
                            
                            <explicit> <locus>F. 2v</locus>
                                <!-- Transcript -->
                                ... ||20||
                                idaṃ kavacam ajñātvā
                                bhajed yo vagalāmukhīm |
                                sa śastraghātam āpnoti
                                tasya vidyā na siddhyati ||21||
                                iti kubjikātantre trailokyavijayanāma kavacaṃ saṃpūrṇaṃ ||
                            </explicit>
                            
                        </msItem>
                        
